news.title: NBCC looks to grow its revenue to Rs 25,000 crore in five years
news.para: The company also aims to increase annual profit to Rs 5,000 crore in five years from Rs 400 crore currently by focusing on real estate development and redeveloping land that are not utilised by other PSUs.

news.title: Ahmedabad: Granted bail, Popular Builders' owner set to leave jail after three years
news.para: Subsequently, various FIRs were filed against the Patels for allegedly occupying land parcels using forged documents. The case for which he was granted bail on Tuesday was registered by Bopal police in November 2022.

news.title: Row at Gurugram's Chintels Paradiso over barricading of unsafe tower
news.para: ​A resident said the labourers had been sent by the builder to cordon off the access to the tower after the Sunday collapse, but some residents sent them away saying any such barricading must be monitored by the administration.

news.title: Blackstone to sell $833 million stake in Embassy REIT
news.para: Blackstone will sell 223.6 million units of Embassy REITs, in one of the biggest block deals this year, at a 7.7% discount to 335.75 rupees per unit price as of Dec. 19, according to the term sheet. The units will be sold via block deals in the secondary market.

news.title: Suraj Estate Developers IPO subscribed 2.42 times on day two of offer
news.para: The category for Retail Individual Investors (RIIs) got subscribed 3.89 times, the quota for non-institutional investors attracted 2.05 times subscription and the category for Qualified Institutional Buyers (QIBs) received 12 per cent subscription.

news.title: UK's LondonMetric, LXI in merger talks to form $4.94 billion property company
news.para: "The boards of LondonMetric and LXI see the potential to bring together two companies with complementary strategic approaches and a key focus on delivering compounding income-led total shareholder returns through the cycle," the commercial property duo said in a joint statement.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government approves Amitabh Kant Committee proposals
news.para: ​The approved recommendations include providing immediate registry and sub-lease deed rights to homebuyers and benefits of 'zero period' to developers in terms of penalties for delay during COVID-19 from April 1, 2020 to March 31, 2022.

news.title: RBI tightens norms to check evergreening of loans by lenders through AIFs
news.para: ​Banks and NBFCs, which are Regulated Entities (RE) under the Reserve Bank of India (RBI), make investments in units of AIFs as part of their regular investment operations.

news.title: HouseEazy raises USD 1 million from investors as seed funding
news.para: ​Other notable investors in the round include India Accelerator, AC Ventures, Agility Ventures, Finvolve Ventures and industry veterans like Pirojsha Godrej (Executive Chairperson at Godrej Properties) and Sandeep Aggarwal (Founder at Droom), the company said in a statement.

news.title: Stability more important than profitability: Shesh Rao, co-founder, BHIVE
news.para: BHIVE Workspace expects to touch Rs 210-200 crore revenue and EBITDA of about Rs 25 crore in FY24. In the next five years, it wants to reach Rs 500 crore revenue.

news.title: About 32 stone crushers in Bijnor to face the heat as deadline to install CCTVs expires
news.para: On December 2, the directorate of geology and mining issued directions that weigh-bridges at these facilities should install CCTV cameras and connect them with the directorate and the district administration before December 18 but the crusher owners failed to do so.

news.title: Construction workers in Jharkhand protest for simplification of registration rules
news.para: Construction workers handed over a memorandum of their demands to the office staff. Earlier, they staged a rally from the Shree Krishna Singh Park to the labour commissioner’s office.

news.title: Ludhiana improvement trust stops transfer of colonies to civic body
news.para: LIT officials justified the move saying that they were yet to recover a large amount in the form of non-construction fee (NCF) from defaulters. Besides, they said that certain properties were left in these colonies for auction, due to which they could not hand them over.

news.title: Nashik civic body plans drive in January 2024 to act against property tax defaulters
news.para: NMC commissioner Ashok Karanjkar had informed civic body officials to meet the property tax collection target of Rs210 crore by December-end this year. This tax collection target is set for the current financial year.

news.title: Kanpur development body plots sold at more than their reserved price
news.para: The KDA in fact has auctioned 405 plots out of a total 480 plots whose estimated reserve price was Rs 76,95,34,809.00 and were sold at the cost of Rs. 152,73,95,406.00.

news.title: Ahmedabad fails to develop transit corridors: Study
news.para: However, unlike several Indian and international cities that have been developed around transit corridors, Ahmedabad has not been able to capitalize on these corridors, claimed the study.

news.title: Pune civic body to reissue tax bills of two lakh properties without discount
news.para: The process to finalise the new bill amounts for them is underway. It is expected to be completed by December-end, paving way for new bills’ issuance,” said Ajit Deshmukh, head of PMC’s property tax department.

news.title: ED registers case against Tulsiani Builders' CMD & MD for loan fraud
news.para: ED registered a case following a complaint lodged by the manager of Punjab National Bank who alleged that Tulsiani Group directors took a loan of Rs 4.63 crore after furnishing forged documents and did not respond to correspondence for recovery of loan amount.

news.title: No verification of tenants? Landlords in Ghaziabad to face action
news.para: The move follows the arrest of several criminals who were staying on rent without verification. Cosp also found out that many criminals were expelled from their districts like Noida, Bulandshahr and Meerut and have been residing in Ghaziabad without proper verification.

news.title: Sweden's SBB gathers residential assets in subsidiary ahead of share sale
news.para: SBB, which has racked up vast debt by buying public property, said in November it was looking for equity partners to help reduce its debt, as it tries to strengthen its financial stability and streamline operations.
